outh Australia|SA]]\n!colspan=|[[Western Australia|WA]]\n!colspan=|[[Tasmania|TAS]]\n!colspan=|[[Australian Capital Territory|ACT]]\n!colspan=|[[Northern Territory|NT]]\n!Total\n!New<br/>cases\n!%<br/>growth\n!Deaths<br/>Nationally\n|-\n|'''Deaths by<br/> State/Territory'''\n|align=right|'''19'''\n|align=right|'''5'''\n|align=right|'''10'''\n|align=right|'''0'''\n|align=right|'''3'''\n|align=right|'''2'''\n|align=right|'''2'''\n|align=right|'''0'''\n|align=right|'''41'''\n|align=right|\n|align=right|\n|align=right|\n|}\n\nNotes:\n# The figures for 4 March include 10 cases from the ''Diamond Princess''. The number repatriated from the ship are included in the state totals as follows: Qld (3), Vic (4), SA (1), WA (2, one of whom died on 1 March).<ref name=princess/><ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert|title=Novel coronavirus (2019-nCoV) health alert|date=2 March 2020|agency=Australian Government Department of Health|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200211190436/https://www.health.gov.au/news/health-alerts/novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov-health-alert|archive-date=11 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n# The figures for 22 March include 26 from the ''Ruby Princess'' cruise ship:<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/coronavirus-australia-ruby-princess-cruise-ship-largest-daily-rise-cases |title=Coronavirus in Australia: 26 infections from Ruby Princess contribute to largest daily rise in cases |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323135639/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/coronavirus-australia-ruby-princess-cruise-ship-largest-daily-rise-cases |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> NSW 18, WA 6, other 2. The number climbed to 133 on 24 March: 107 in NSW, 26 interstate.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/> A passenger from the ship died on 24 March in Sydney. Since then, more tha